 smile was one of malicious intent. &quot;I'm Andy, who are you?&quot; The man looked up at him. &quot;I'm George. You can call me Georgie.&quot; Andy smiled. This city was so much different than the home he had grown up ini. He was happy there until he learned that his life had been a lie. His parents had come across him when he was little wandering the streets and taken him in. Only did they tell him about this a few short weeks ago. Ever siince then he went in search for his family. Not finding anything but small bits of information about his parents and more about his sister than his father or mother. And that was only her name. &quot;So how do you know Jerron?&quot; Andy asked hoping to understand the malicious look. &quot;Well, he is a friend of ours, you see we always go to clubs to hang out, it was just a few weeks ago that him and his group, there were eight of them, left the clubs. See we had a bit of a disagreement and so I wanted to make a mence.&quot; Understanding swept through him. This was not a friend, but atleast he might be able to help. Reaching a hand into his finely tailored suit Andy felt for the small blade the man he called father had given him before he left. It was the one he learned to fight with. In his family's home Andy was always curious with the more primative weapons such as knives and the martial arts. There were a rare few left that knew those arts well enough to teach in his home city. Everyone there was a peacful sort and Andy deeply missed his home. But he had to find his sister before he could go. He only hoped he could conveince her to come back with him. Looking down to the mean little man leading them down the street, Andy slowly started to pull the blade from his coat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rillen@fantasystoriesforum>Rillen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SR