<br>
The sky was beautiful. At least in Nefertiti's eyes. Pale, soft, and grey. It's color was completely unwavering, not a single cloud dare creep across it's magnificantness. Her lips wanted to smile, but the sorrow that clung to her, no matter what her mood, kept it just as it was. Glancing from side to side they paused. Her voice was tiny, hushed, yet sweet as always and unfearful. &quot;Where to first, sweetpea?&quot; A little sigh escaped her bubblegum lips and she rested her head against his arm. Where to first? How about back to a few months ago when the group was all together? How about into the future to better times? How about a magical land of happiness and rainbows where all of this @#%$ would disappear? There was always the corner store, after all they were having a sale of some sort. One of those once a year sales they have every three months. Rubbing her hand up and down the arm of Jerron's she clung to she waited for him to answer. Staying home would have been so much more easier. Less stress of being in public. But then again, they did have eachother. One foot in front of the other was all it took. And in doing just that she made her way towards the store with her arms still clutching Jerron's.  <p><br>
