<br>
Lifting the plates from the table, Carmen walked them over to the trash can. She tossed the old contents into the garbage, then walked the plates to the sink. Turning on the water, she began to scrub the plates clean. It was weird. She never was a very neat girl, but ever since Carmen had moved in permanently with Jerron and Neferiti, she'd delevoped this weird desire to keep everything clean. It wasn't like they ever had visitors, but other than eachother it was all they had. So, she took pride in it. <br>
<br>
When all the dishes were done, dried, and put away, Carmen wiped down the counter and the table. Looking around, she decided the kitchen looked well enough and tossed the sponge back into the sink. <br>
<br>
Making her way out into the living room, she scanned the place, making sure she had grabbed the last of the beer bottles. Which, of course, she had earlier that morning while the rest of the crew was still asleep. <br>
<br>
Carmen stood in the middle of the room, she had nothing to do... Devin was asleep, Jerron and Neferiti were out.<br>
<br>
Looking down at her body, she decided what she needed to go do. Take a shower. <br>
<br>
Walking back to the room, Nefer and herself shared, Carmen grabbed a clean bra and pair underwear. She decided she'd just come back and change into her clothes when she was done... A nice hot shower did sound relaxing right then... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ryvian>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 209<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/23/02 7:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> again</span><hr size=1> Walking out of the ally, Andy looked at his hands. They were covered in blood. The man had hit him first he kept telling himself. That man hit him first, but he didn't see the knife. looking at the crowd he shoved his hands back into his pockets. Decideing he would walk to the nearest store and see if he could wash the blood off, Andy started to move towards the first shop he could see. Walking in he saw it was a general store and there were only a few people in it. There was a young woman who looked to be almost sick clinging onto another man who didn't look much better, an elderly couple and a few single shoppers. Walking to the clerk he smiled. &quot;Do you have a restroom here?&quot; The clerk smiled and pointed to the back of the store. Nodding his thanks Andy hurried to the back.<br>
<br>
