<br>
The door swung easily open without Mika having to lay a finger on it.  Which was a good thing, for in her left hand she carried a large brown sack filled with meat and vegitable curries.  In her right hand she carried a small black backpak that contained her only possesions.  Almost as if she had never been gone and the events of the last few months had never happened, she waltzed into the large common room and flung herself down on the sofa.  she reached into the bag and took out a small box of curry and threw it at devin who was reclined in the corner.  it landed with a warm plop on his chest but did not spill.  <br>
   &quot;you better start eating before it gets cold&quot;  Mika warned.  without waiting for a response she got up to see who else was home.  a box of curry in one hand and chopsticks in the other she walked toward the sound of the running shower.  she kicked open the bathroom door which had been left unlatched and called into the steam filled room through a full mouth, &quot;hullo?&quot;<br>
<br>
