whatever, something Egyptian like hers, but Marcus? ...Brother? She had a brother? What did he want? Why was he here? Ooo! Her parents never told her about this! Her parents... They had something to do with this... Her brother... The offspring of those horrid people... Ice collected in her eyes and her muscles tightened. Parents. Her parents. She felt the grotesque markings of her past sting her abdomen. Parents. Bound to her forever. Cruel past. The pain. The hurt. Abuse? Trauma. Scars. Blood stained. Her blood. Their hands. Parents. Family. Returned… Every pain stricken memory in her mind screamed out at once in a harmonious call for help. The heart gripping noise echoed from the depths of her brain and ripped at her soul. Jerron’s arm was dropped instantly and her eyes turned on Andy. Stormy gray and dripping with a hate so deep not even her gods themselves could save her from it. <br>
<br>
“Try Egypt”<br>
<br>
Nefertiti thrusts her shoulder into Andy as she pushes her way by. She thought Jerron might have called out to her, or maybe someone else did… It didn’t mater she couldn’t hear them, not now. Not as she ran on, to a place she once knew, a place that hopefully was the same as it was then. An old refuge. No, she couldn’t hear them now… Her mind was gone. Images, flashbacks, just like in the movies… only real. They were of her past, of her trials, of her grievances. Of her pain… Always pain. Because there’s no better word. <br>
