<br>
Mika stood and stared blankly at Devin.  Part of her wanted to answer him, to tell him exactly what had happened to her; to cry on his shoulder.  But that was not her style and she knew it.  She had also decided that some things were better forgotten, and she desperatly wanted this to be one of them.  So instead, she took another bite of curry and sat down on the couch.  <br>
     &quot;how ya doing?&quot;  she mumbled as she licked sauce from the corner of her mouth.  <br>
<br>
a dagger cut into her heart.  Neferititi was near and her emotions were high.  Mika called out through time and space, whispered in her friends ear, &quot;come.&quot;<br>
