t the others might return just as Mika did and the past two months will have been nothing more than a terrible nightmare that finally - FINALLY will come to an end...<br>
<br>
~*(Nefertiti *~ Come... She heard it echo through her mind. She knew the voice well. It couldn't be. She almost didn't want it to be. For if it was... then it would cause the wounds she was trying so hard to mend to reopen and then close and she wasn't sure if she could handle such a thing. And so she continued to run. Tears rolling down her cheeks and the wind burning them into her skin with its icy kiss. She had finally snapped... Thought she heard her* voice again... She was hearing things. Crazy. No other explination. Wanted something so bad she made it true. Lies. She* was long gone. Never to return. Remember? But her* voice... it was here, it was real. How? No. Lies. Wrong. Crazy. <br>
She needed to be safe. She needed to feel protected. So she ran. No one would find her where she was going. They couldn't. She didn't want them to. Her feet slowed as she came upon large steel gates. The fimiliar &quot;F&quot; was twisted and entwined in metal vines high up on the gate. No one knew what the &quot;F&quot; stood for, but in her eyes it was beautiful. <br>
A child's voice came from the sandbox 80 feet to her right. The sun shown through as other children giggled near by. &quot;One day I'll own this whoooole thing. I will. And I'll change my name to &quot;F&quot; so that the gates will mean ME. And you can come and stay here with me. We can live here together and be King and Queen until we're old, and then we'll give it to our grandchildren and they can be Prince and Princess forever, and they'll carry on my &quot;F&quot; name. I just need to make up the name first.&quot; Little girl with a little boy. Sitting in a little sand box. Bright blue eyes and dark brown hair up in pig tails with bows that matched the turquoise shirt she wore. The sun faded and the children were long since gone. A soul hadn't set foot on these grounds for years. Abandoned and lost. Nefertiti squeezed through the gates and ran through the large court yard that she had spent the majority of her childhood in. No one knew of her secret love for this place, no one had the slightest clue... except for one. She slammed open the enormous wooden front doors. Everything was dimmer now. Unlike the dead and unkept yards, the inside's only flaw was dust and cobwebs. All of the furniture had been left as well as all the furnishings. Thick draps hung over the windows and kept out the light. Nefertiti turned around ever-so slowly. It was all the same... A heavy pounding on the steps jerked her entire body to face them. A tiny giggle came from higher up on the stair well just beyond it's turn. <br>
&quot;Titi! Come on!&quot; <br>
&quot;W... wait!&quot;<br>
Her feet clomped up each turn of steps as fast as she could. The giggling called her up, up, and up. These stairs were always exhausting. Letting out a breathless sigh, she took the final step and reached the top. Gods damn those things, pain in the ass. <br>
&quot;Titi, hurry!&quot;<br>
Again, she found herself trailing after the youthful voice. Through this hall, turn onto this one, past these doors... this castle like house was gigantic! An utter maze of coridors, hallways, wings, and rooms. The voice and laughter grew quieter...<br>
&quot;Wait! Not so fast! I can't keep up!&quot;<br>
Running again. The noise had all but died leaving only the pounding of her feet to keep away the silence. She ran almost frantically now, knowing and not knowing where she was going and trying to find that voice again. Her hand grabbed onto a door knob and thrust open the door. Out of breath she looked blankly into the room. De-hehehehe. That laugh! From behind her it rang out and made her jump. Spining around behind she was greated with-nothing. And the laughter was gone...<br>
<br>
